        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;">Andhra Fish Curry</h2>

        <img style="padding-left:225px;width:400px;height:400px" src="https://www.desicookingrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/1614016740_maxresdefault-250x250.jpg" alt="Andhra Fish Curry">
        <div id="en">
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Ingredients:</p>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px"> For Marinating Fish:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 4-6 pieces of fish (preferably a firm-fleshed fish like Rohu or Catfish)</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
                <li> Salt to taste</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">For the Curry:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 2 tablespoons oil</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon mustard seeds,fenugreek seeds,cumin seeds</li>
                <li> 1 large onion,2 tomatoes</li>
                <li> 2-3 green chilies, slit, 2-3 dried red chilies</li>
                <li> 1/2 cup tamarind pulp</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon red chili powder,Salt</li>
                <li> 2 tablespoons coriander powder,1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
                <li> 1 sprig curry leaves, coriander leaves for garnish</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Instructions:</p>
            <br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">1. Marinate the Fish:</li><ul>
                <li> In a bowl, mix the fish pieces with turmeric powder and salt.</li>
                <li>Allow them to marinate for at least 15-20 minutes.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">2. Prepare TamarindPulp:</li><ul>

                <li> Soak tamarind in warm water and extract the pulp. Set it aside.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">3. Prepare theCurry:</li><ul>
                <li> Heat oil in a deep pan over medium-high heat.</li>
                <li> Add mustard seeds and let them splutter.</li>
                <li> Add fenugreek seeds and cumin seeds. Sauté briefly until they release their aroma.</li>
                <li> Add chopped onions and green chilies. Sauté until the onions become translucent.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">4. Add theFish:</li><ul>
                <li> Carefully place the marinated fish pieces into the simmering curry.</li>
                <li> Cover and cook for about 10-15 minutes or until the fish is fully cooked and flakes easily.</li>
                <li> Mix well and sauté for a couple of minutes until the raw smell of the spices disappears.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">5. Add Tomatoes and TamarindPulp:</li><ul>
                <li> Add the chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and the oil starts to separate from the mixture.</li>
                <li> Pour in the tamarind pulp and mix well. Add salt to taste.</li>
                <li>Stir and let it simmer for a few minutes to combine the flavors.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">6. AddWater:</li><ul>
                <li> Add enough water to achieve your desired consistency for the curry.</li>
                <li>This will depend on how thick or thin you prefer your fish curry. </li>
                <li> Cover and cook for about 10-15 minutes or until the fish is fully cooked and flakes easily.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">7. AddSpices:</li><ul>
                <li> Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, and coriander powder.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">8. Garnish andServe:</li><ul>
                <li> Garnish with fresh curry leaves and coriander leaves.</li>
                <li> Serve Chepala Pulusu hot with steamed rice. The tangy and spicy flavors make it a delightful dish.</li>
            </ul><p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">Enjoy your homemade Andhra Fish Curry!</p>
